MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 4a8927dcb8d02334aa834fd3c6f2de67, type: 3}
  m_Name: ClueDatabase
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ClueDatabase
  allCombos:
  - comboID: 1
    questionText: When does Thornwall draw its walls inward?
    clueText: The castle does not sleep,  it exhales. Three times a night the walls
      breathe inward. Do not be standing in the east corridor when it does.
    correctAnswer: Three times a night
  - comboID: 2
    questionText: What distinguishes a Bounded from an infiltrator?
    clueText: The Bounded do not eat. If you see someone at the banquet table, they
      are not Bounded.
    correctAnswer: The Bounded do not eat
  - comboID: 3
    questionText: How does the castle mark its longest-held prisoners?
    clueText: The castle marks its oldest prisoners with cold hands. The longer they
      have been Bounded, the colder the skin. The ones in the lower vaults have not
      been warm in decades.
    correctAnswer: Cold hands
  - comboID: 4
    questionText: How many doors in Thornwall open outward?
    clueText: There is only one door in Thornwall that opens outward. The castle
      never built another, it does not expect anything to leave.
    correctAnswer: One
  - comboID: 5
    questionText: How do the garden wolves detect a free person?
    clueText: The wolves in the garden do not hunt by sight. They hunt by the warmth
      of free blood. Witch blood runs warmer than Bounded blood.
    correctAnswer: By the warmth of free blood
  - comboID: 6
    questionText: How many times has the Heart Gate been opened?
    clueText: The Heart Gate has been opened twice in the castle's lifetime. Both
      times, the one who opened it did not come back as the curse consumes them.
    correctAnswer: Twice
  - comboID: 7
    questionText: "When do the castle\u2019s bells toll?"
    clueText: "The castle\u2019s bells do not toll for time. They toll when a prisoner\u2019s
      mind breaks."
    correctAnswer: "When a prisoner\u2019s mind breaks"
  - comboID: 8
    questionText: What do the mirrors in Thornwall reveal?
    clueText: The mirrors in Thornwall do not show reflections. They show who the
      castle wants you to see.
    correctAnswer: Who the castle wants you to see
  - comboID: 9
    questionText: When do the staircases of Thornwall shift?
    clueText: The staircases shift only at midnight. If you climb before then, you
      will never reach the same floor twice.
    correctAnswer: At midnight
  - comboID: 10
    questionText: What fuels the lanterns in the west wing?
    clueText: The lanterns in the west wing burn without flame. They are lit by the
      breath of the Bounded.
    correctAnswer: The breath of the Bounded
  - comboID: 11
    questionText: What happens if the dungeon doors whisper your name?
    clueText: The dungeon doors whisper names. If you hear your own, you will not
      leave alive.
    correctAnswer: You will not leave alive
  - comboID: 12
    questionText: "When does the castle\u2019s heart quiet?"
    clueText: "The castle\u2019s heart beats louder when strangers enter. It quiets
      only when blood is spilled."
    correctAnswer: When blood is spilled
